  <a ref-type="fig" rid="fig01" href="#fig01">Fig. 1
   <span class="italic">A</span>
  </a> for the pollinator and in 
  <a ref-type="fig" rid="fig01" href="#fig01">Fig. 1
   <span class="italic">B</span>
  </a> for the plant. We can then calculate, for each real network, the parameters 
  <div class="inline-formula">
   <div id="i39" class="math">
    <div class="mrow">
     <span stretchy="false" class="mo">⟨</span>
     <div class="msub">
      <span class="mi">γ</span>
      <span class="mi">P</span>
     </div>
